  "text": "The ext_authz filter implementation in Envoy v1.31.2 provides external authorization capabilities with bypass, passthrough, and decision handling logic across HTTP and network filters.\n\n**Per-Route Bypass Configuration (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/):**\nThe HTTP filter implements per-route control through the `FilterConfigPerRoute` class (ext_authz.h:231-273) which contains a `disabled_` flag (line 272) that enables bypassing authorization checks on specific routes. The `disabled()` getter method (ext_authz.h:261) returns this flag. The per-route configuration is retrieved in `Filter::getPerRouteFlags()` (ext_authz.cc:810-827) using `Http::Utility::resolveMostSpecificPerFilterConfig<FilterConfigPerRoute>()`. When `skip_check_` is true (set from the disabled flag in decodeHeaders at line 229), the filter immediately returns `Continue` status (line 231), bypassing the external authorization call.\n\n**Authorization Decision and Immediate Response Path (source/extensions/filters/http/ext_authz/):**\nThe primary authorization decision handler is `Filter::onComplete()` (ext_authz.cc:403-769) which processes three response statuses from the authorization service:\n\n1. **OK Status (CheckStatus::OK)**: Lines 432-675 handle approved requests with header mutations, query parameter modifications, and route cache clearing based on `config_->clearRouteCache()` (lines 436-441).\n\n2. **Denied Status (CheckStatus::Denied)**: Lines 678-736 implement the immediate response path by calling `decoder_callbacks_->sendLocalReply()` with the denied response status code, body, and headers (lines 717-735).\n\n3. **Error Status (CheckStatus::Error)**: Lines 739-767 handle authorization service failures, with fail-open behavior controlled by `config_->failureModeAllow()` (line 744).\n\nThe `FilterConfig` class (ext_authz.h:57-223) stores global filter configuration including `clear_route_cache_` (line 180), `failureModeAllow()` method (line 69), and other control flags.\n\n**Network Filter Implementation (source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/):**\nThe network filter implements similar authorization decision logic in its `Filter::onComplete()` method (ext_authz.cc:72-130), closing connections for denied or error responses (lines 105-115) and continuing for approved traffic (lines 116-129).\n\n**Common Infrastructure (source/extensions/filters/common/ext_authz/):**\nThe gRPC client implementation (ext_authz_grpc_impl.cc) processes authorization responses in `onSuccess()` (lines 106-143) and `onFailure()` (lines 146-156). The HTTP client implementation (ext_authz_http_impl.cc) constructs responses using header matchers to determine which response headers should be forwarded to clients, upstream servers, or converted to dynamic metadata. The `check_request_utils` module provides utilities for constructing CheckRequest messages from HTTP and TCP attributes.\n\n**Note on Caching:**\nWhile explicit response caching is not implemented in the ext_authz filter itself, the filter provides a `clear_route_cache_` configuration option that clears the route cache when authorization responses modify routing-relevant headers, preventing stale cached routing decisions.\n"
}

